caption: The service is great. We had the duck confit which came with a generous portion of pulled duck meat on a bed of various lettuces with a huge fried duck egg on top. I liked it and would order it again. I had the fried chicken sandwich. Really crispy and dark meat with a pimento like cheese.  A nice slaw would have been better. The meat was a little dry.

If you are heading here for a charcuterie board hold off. The piles (yes I mean piles) of cheese looked and tasted as if they were from the bottom of a shredded cheese bag. Instead of giving blocks of cheese they were piles of shredded cheese... not exactly the classic cheese board one is looking to enjoy.
Wonderful wine and tasty nosh.
Great service

I was here last winter with a large group. Ready to spend some big bucks to celebrate a success at work, they informed us their stove was broken. As a result I think I've tried all their appetizers and they served us most of their entrees not requiring the oven as small plates.
It's a really cute wine bar but the service was really slow
Great wine
Food was good,  wine was great,  service was awesome.  Would go back.  Very low key.

Enolo has a great happy hour and nice bites to enjoy as well. Our server Jacob was helpful with helping us decide what to order and made sure we had all that we needed. The table next to us accidentally knocked a bottle off the table but the staff was quick to clean up the spill and shards, and very kind in ensuring everyone was ok and no one was stained. It was barely an inconvenience but the staff still treated us to a complimentary round of drinks.

The food was absolutely amazing. We came here looking for a light snack and that's what we accomplished. Everything we ordered was off the charts when it came to taste. The reason it got two stars is completely because of the service I had. My waiter was Jacob H according to our receipt. From the moment Jacob (didn't) greet us he had a terrible attitude. We ordered drinks, and we're never asked to see an ID. After ordering drinks, we attempted to order food with issues of it all being premade and being told we were unable to change the meals to fit our allergy specification. We asked Jacob multiple times to refill our water and time and time again he forgot about us. I had to remind him twice to bring my bill, and this was on a Tuesday night when tables were empty. This can't be blamed on it being busy, this was completely because of Jacobs poor attitude that night. By the end of our service I was irritated and didn't even believe Jacob deserved a tip, I would have slept well at night knowing I didn't give him one with the attitude he had towards our table on the one night we were in town. Luckily for him I still gave him a nice tip in hopes it would help lift his spirits for the rest of the tables he had that night. I hope Jacobs attitude gets better or he gets more training soon. There are thousands of restaurant options in the city, and Jacobs poor attitude will keep me from going back.
Great worldly wine list and happy hour prices are nice!

Nice place!
A little over priced but good wine collection

My friends and I came here on a Saturday night in May. We were looking for restaurants with a charcuterie board and this seemed like a good option.  The restaurant was smaller than I thought. We were also seated by the door which was chilly on the night we went. Service was pretty good from what I remembered.  We ordered truffle fries and calamari for apps. They were both pretty good. The prosciutto bruschetta was also a great choice. What was not a great choice though was the charcuterie board. The board was at least $15 and the meats and cheeses were tiny. Nothing too exciting over here.  For drinks we had the wine flights. It was $24 if I remember correctly and pretty good. Worth a shot to try this place but most likely won't be back.

Nice place to visit once... It was too loud inside we could barely talk to each other... Food was pricy and small. Good taste though. Service was good too. I'd not give an outstanding on anything. Just another regular placer...
Went for a networking event, bartenders were really great, appetizers we're quite yummy actually, the wine of course was delightful. An overall lovely experience.

Pleasant small cozy bar,  I'm of Hispanic descent and I loved the salsa music playing in the background. The interior design is nice and golden. Clean, outside seating available. Food and small select choices of beer available.

Didn’t get any food here, but the service was good enough, and prices were ok. Would need to get food to rate higher. The place was ok over all but not super memorable.

Great wine selection and delicious food! Came with a group and we felt like we were a complete hassle to the waiter, even though we werent. He also wouldn't itemize the bill even into 2 or 3 checks, he just wanted to do even splits. After working in the industry for 6 years and a table asks for split checks, it really is not a big deal, especially when the rush is over. Moral of the story don't order a $350 tab if one of you isn't prepared to put it all on your card, or if you want to do an even split even though you may have only ordered 1 drink. Makes total sense.... not.

We paid $25 for a bottle of wine and a Charcuterie board. What a great deal, not only for a restaurant in downtown Chicago, but a great deal in any city!!!  I would definitely recommend this place for a nice snack and some wine!

Wine flights and small plates makes a great combo at this "wine cafe". The ambiance fits, and makes for a great place to stop before dinner, or even for dinner. Their house-made ricotta is amazing, so make sure you try some!

Fantastic wine bar, conveniently located in River North. Upscale, lively crowd and fantastic, friendly bartenders. Their wines are great, however, their spirits are also wonderful.

Enolo Wine Cafe is a trendy restaurant and bar that serves new American eats. They have a full bar with wine, beer, and spirits so don't be too deterred by the name. Everything I've tried here was delicious: sausage pizza, kale salad, burrata with grilled vegetables, and tagliatelle. I didn't get to sit at a table since they were full but the bar seating was adequate. Customer service was very commendable and the ambiance was warmly modern. For those who care, they played awesome R&B from early 2000s. Overall, Enolo is a recommendable place for a fun dinner date.
Great food, staff and drinks. The food is more amazing each bite.

Great place! We are new to Chicago and our bartender, Dana, had great insights for us. She was very knowledgeable and gave us some great advice on what areas to check out. The food was delicious and the staff was very welcoming.

This place is great! Perfect first date spot too! I tried a couple of the wine flights-- the Premiere Cru wasn't to my liking--- it was a bit too earthy for me. I liked the Bienvenue a Bordeaux a lot better. I also got a glass of the Domaine Sigalas, Assyrtiko-Athini from Santorini, which I really liked. I know it probably sounds like I'm a boozer... which I'm not going to lie, I kind of am.  The place is really dark and intimate... a lot darker than I was expecting after visiting their website, but it was a cold, rainy day and so I didn't mind the atmosphere--- it seemed to fit the mood perfectly. The server was really knowledgeable about all of the wines, and very helpful as well.  I definitely would go back to try a few more of the wines. I'll have to try some of the food items as well!
